# LINE MINI App Manual QA Checklist

## LIFF Browser Tests

- [ ] Opens from Developing LIFF URL inside LINE
- [ ] Correct LIFF ID is used for Developing (and Review/Published when testing those)
- [ ] Auth exchange succeeds and local session is created
- [ ] No redirect/rewrite occurs before `liff.init()` completes
- [ ] Bottom actions are visible above safe area (test on both iOS and Android)
- [ ] Post-LINE 26.7.0 header/dropdown behavior works correctly
- [ ] Android edge-to-edge rendering (March 2026+) tested

## External Browser Tests

- [ ] App opens from endpoint URL outside LINE
- [ ] If login is required, external-browser login path works (`withLoginOnExternalBrowser`)
- [ ] Unsupported LIFF-browser-only features show fallback UI
- [ ] Open-in-LINE affordance appears where appropriate

## Security Tests

- [ ] Backend rejects forged or blank `idToken`
- [ ] Backend rejects ID token with wrong `iss`, `aud`, or expired `exp`
- [ ] Backend creates or links the correct user after valid verification
- [ ] No `LINE_CHANNEL_SECRET` exposed in frontend bundle
- [ ] `liff.getProfile()` output is never sent to backend as identity proof

## Review Readiness

- [ ] Review endpoint deploy is accessible
- [ ] Channel metadata matches actual service behavior
- [ ] Privacy policy matches data flow
- [ ] Verified-only features are not assumed in Published before approval
